title: For Sale:  CHINESE / NORINCO ~ 56S AK-47 PRE-BAN/Early Sile Import UNFIRED IN BOX w/ ALL ACCESSORIES..
postcontent: Here's a super nice, unfired, Pre-Ban Chinese Norinco Type 56-S...the semi-auto version of the Chinese military AK. Chambered for the 7.62x39mm, this rifle has a 16-1/4" chrome lined barrel with threaded muzzle brake and bayonet lug. The Chinese AK's are highly respected and are among the best available but thanks to the Clinton era import ban, they have been getting harder and harder to come by. The thicker 1.5mm stamped receivers are more durable than many of the 1mm thick Eastern block rifles, and the Chinese guns really are built to last. This rifle is in excellent original condition and I'd grade it about 99% overall. There is no rust or pitting. The stocks are in excellent condition with just a few tiny handling marks (these rifles seemed to ship new with a few handling marks). This rifle was a relatively early Sile import and has a blued bolt and the /66\ arsenal marking on the left side of the trunnion. The serial numbered parts are all properly matching, including the bayonet! The mechanics are in perfect working order (AK's are good for that!) and the bore is excellent. Internal inspection confirms that this rifle is absolutely unfired since it left the factory! It comes in the original box that numbers to the gun and includes all three 30-round mags, cleaning rod, bayonet with scabbard, sling (still sealed in plastic), buttstock cleaning kit, port cleaning tool, oil bottle, and owner's manual. They just don't get any better!

title: For Sale:  Pre-War WW2 Winchester US M1 Garand Oct 1941 Early
postcontent: Exceptionally early Winchester M1 Garand US rifle...this Garand was produced by the Winchester arsenal in October of 1941, over a month prior to the attack on Pearl Harbor. A favorite of collectors, Winchester commenced production of the M1 in December of 1940.Having seen some degree of rebuild, the rifle does retain several Winchester components, including the bolt, with some clear later-war time replacement parts, among them the Springfield production rear sight and gas assembly. Additionally, the rifle is fitted with a desirable Danish VAR barrel-regarded by shooters as one of the best barrels ever produced for the M1-which confirms it's post-war service with the Danish military. A fine example for the shooter with broad-ranging collector appeal, this early Winchester M1 would be suited to any military or WWII arms collection.Very good condition, the rifle has seen no post-service refinish and retains around 70% phosphate finish with the small parts showing the most wear. No rust or deep pitting are present and all markings are correct, with no import mark, suggesting that this weapon was imported by the CMP.

title: For Sale:  96FS... with a story
postcontent: So... 10 years ago I went to Air Assault with the National Guard. I left, came back, and my roommate was gone and so was my brand new Beretta 96FS. 10 years later, Tigard Police call me up and tell me that I could pick up my hand gun! Seems it got into some bad hands, and was picked up in a drug sting. They held it in evidence trying to pin it on someone. Strange world, right? Anyways, I like the weapon, but bought a new car. So, I could use the money. The weapon comes in an evidence box!!! You'll have to buy up a carrying case for about 20 bucks, but it is in great shape. Unless the FBI used it as a trainer and restored it, it has less than 100 rounds down the chamber. A tiny scratch in the finish, you may not see above the hand guard is evident. The rifling looks clean. It's probably just been sitting for a loooooong time. (No rust evident)As far as the weapon is concerned. It's .40, I like them better than Glocks, but not as much as M&Ps. Single stack, solid weapon. If you served, you probably know exactly how to handle these things and that is a plus! The FS has no real safety. It has a decocking lever, instead of a safety. So, it is shooters preference. I never liked the standard Beretta's safeties, so I like this model better. Anyways, that is the story and the deal! We'll do a transfer that will come out of the price, and if you want. We got 100 rounds to test fire it, if you have a range you want to meet at!
